# Node.js Mock Server Project Structure Guide

This is a Node.js Mock Server project based on Swagger/OpenAPI specifications, designed for rapid generation and provision of API mock data.

## Core File Structure

### Main Entry Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and script configuration
- [src/server.ts](mdc:src/server.ts) - Express server main file, handling all API requests
- [src/mock-generator.ts](mdc:src/mock-generator.ts) - Core logic for generating mock data from Swagger files
- [src/cli/generate-mock.ts](mdc:src/cli/generate-mock.ts) - CLI tool entry point for generating mock files

### Type Definitions

- [src/types/swagger.ts](mdc:src/types/swagger.ts) - Zod type definitions for Swagger documents

### Examples and Configuration

- [demo/swagger.yaml](mdc:demo/swagger.yaml) - Example Swagger file (Petstore API)
- [mock/](mdc:mock/) - Generated mock data directory, organized by API paths

## Project Architecture

1. **Mock Generator**: Parses Swagger YAML files and automatically generates mock data based on schema definitions
2. **Mock Server**: File system-based routing supporting path parameters and HTTP method matching
3. **CLI Tool**: Provides command-line interface for generating mock files

## Technology Stack

- TypeScript + Node.js
- Express.js as web server
- Zod for type validation
- YAML parser
- fs-extra for file operations
- Commander.js for CLI tools
